<subSubSection pageId="142" pageNumber="143" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="142.[151,1437,1707,2003]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis box="[151,233,1708,1733]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Leaves</emphasis>
undivided, rarely pinnate; veins not raised or slightly raised and triangular in cross-section adaxially; pinnae 1(1–3) per side of rachis. 
<emphasis box="[552,725,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Inflorescences</emphasis>
unbranched, rarely branched; staminate flowers deciduous after anthesis, rarely persistent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="143" lastPageNumber="144" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="142.[151,1437,1707,2003]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,556,1822,1848]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
From 2°20’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[716,800,1822,1848]" degrees="7" direction="north" minutes="10" orientation="latitude" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" precision="925" value="7.1666665">7°10’N</geoCoordinate>
and 52°50’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[967,1075,1822,1848]" degrees="58" direction="west" minutes="50" orientation="longitude" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" precision="925" value="-58.833332">58°50’W</geoCoordinate>
in the northeastern Amazon region of 
<collectingCountry box="[264,376,1861,1887]" name="Suriname" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Suriname</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[432,608,1861,1887]" name="French Guiana" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, with an outlying specimen in 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1057,1861,1887]" name="Guyana" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, at 373(100–800) m elevation in lowland rainforest (
<figureCitation box="[381,468,1900,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="140.[151,255,1334,1357]" captionTargetBox="[172,1417,304,1311]" captionTargetId="figure@140.[151,1436,284,1326]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 38. Distribution maps of Geonoma spinescens, G. stricta subsp. stricta, G. stricta subsp. antioquiensis, and G. stricta subsp. arundinacea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3538439" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3538439/files/figure.png" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="142.[151,1437,1707,2003]" lastBlockId="143.[151,1437,152,371]" lastPageId="143" lastPageNumber="144" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
Two specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[454,628,1939,1965]" name="French Guiana" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[646,1048,1939,1965]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">de Granville 4803, Le Prieur s. n.</emphasis>
) are unusual in having branched inflorescences with 2–3, stouter rachillae, and one has a pinnate leaf (the only one in this subspecies). They are recognized as the 
<taxonomicName box="[404,503,152,178]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="neglecta">
<emphasis box="[404,503,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">neglecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphotype. One of these specimens (
<emphasis box="[959,1126,153,178]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">Le Prieur s. n.</emphasis>
) has “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1203,1423,152,178]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="neglecta">
<emphasis box="[1203,1423,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">Geonoma neglecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” written, in Trail’s hand-writing, on the label. This specimen was illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wessels Boer, J." box="[1087,1327,190,216]" journalOrPublisher="Verhandelingen der Koninklijke Nederlandsche Akademie van Wetenschappen, Afdeeling Natuurkunde. Tweede Sectie" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" pagination="1 - 202" part="58" refId="ref124810" refString="Wessels Boer, J. (1968) The geonomoid palms. Verhandelingen der Koninklijke Nederlandsche Akademie van Wetenschappen, Afdeeling Natuurkunde. Tweede Sectie 58: 1 - 202." title="The geonomoid palms" type="journal article" year="1968">Wessels Boer (1968</bibRefCitation>
, plate V) and determined by him as 
<emphasis box="[462,605,229,255]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dammer ex Burret" authorityYear="1930" box="[462,601,229,255]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bartlettii">G. bartlettii</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, the 
<typeStatus box="[777,827,229,255]" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">type</typeStatus>
of that name was destroyed and it is treated here as an excluded name. Two specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[630,742,268,294]" name="Suriname" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">Suriname</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[759,1144,268,294]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">Sastre 1567, Wessels Boer 1558</emphasis>
), with larger leaves and inflorescences with persistent staminate flowers appear more like those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1823" box="[1092,1250,306,332]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pycnostachys">
<emphasis box="[1092,1250,306,332]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">pycnostachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Martius" box="[151,380,345,371]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="stricta" subSpecies="arundinacea">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[232,380,345,371]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">arundinacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These are recognized as the 
<emphasis box="[726,787,345,371]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">large</emphasis>
morphotype.
</paragraph>
